<h3><strong>Govinda says he asked Sajid Nadiadwala to help Yashvardhan&#39;s career</strong></h3>

<p>While talking to ANI, <a href="https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/exclusives/exclusive-interview-sunita-ahuja-breaks-silence-on-family-fight-between-govinda-and-krushna-abhishek-1398321">Govinda</a> expressed that he didn&rsquo;t want his political career to affect his family or have an adverse effect on his kids. Hence, he left politics for them. The veteran Bollywood actor also revealed asking O&#39;Romeo producer Sajid Nadiadwala to help kickstart his son&rsquo;s career. Apparently, Nadiadwala obliged his request and offered Yash his cabin to guide him, and further helped him learn different aspects of filmmaking.</p>

<p>Having said that, Govinda admitted that he wasn&rsquo;t asked for anything else. The Partner star divulged, &ldquo;Aur mujhse jada pucha nahi gaya (And no one consulted me much.) Aur aise ek mahol ghar mein taiyaar tha, ki jisme ki main rishtey mai na kaamyaab hun. (The environment at home was such that I am unsuccessful in the relationship.)&rdquo;</p>

