<h3><strong>Mona Singh calls out women&rsquo;s expiry date in Bollywood</strong></h3>

<p><a href="https://www.pinkvilla.com/cinema/meet-the-actor-who-won-dance-show-landed-an-iconic-tv-role-froze-her-eggs-to-focus-on-acting-played-kareena-kapoors-sister-in-her-debut-film-1400268">Mona Singh</a>&rsquo;s impressive filmography boasts of some popular characters like Mona Sahastrabuddhe from 3 Idiots, Gurpreet Kaur Chaddha from Laal Singh Chaddha, and Simi Kaler from Border 2. But in some of them, the actress in her 40s played characters who are older than her.</p>

<p>While talking to PTI, Singh opined that she hasn&rsquo;t cared about her on-screen age because she is very confident and knows who she is. For her, there&rsquo;s nothing to prove, which is why she keeps taking risks. Having said that, the Jassi Jaissi Koi Nahin star is often asked, &lsquo;Why are you so old on screen?&rsquo; To this, she responds that it doesn&#39;t matter. &ldquo;It&#39;s the character that I&#39;m playing, and it really excites me,&rdquo; Mona expressed.</p>

<p>Having said that, she highlighted that it&rsquo;s sad that Bollywood is the only industry where women come with an expiry date. &ldquo;Whereas men in their 60s can still play the romantic leads, women can&#39;t,&rdquo; expressed the actress, adding that she has never really cared about that because she didn&rsquo;t want to be that.</p>

<p>Talking about her work front, Mona started the year by playing a don in Vir Das&rsquo;s directorial debut film, <a href="https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/reviews/happy-patel-khatarnak-jasoos-movie-review-aamir-khan-and-vir-das-film-is-all-about-read-between-the-lines-1399948">Happy Patel: Khatarnak Jasoos</a>. Backed by Aamir Khan&rsquo;s production house, the movie also stars Das along with Mithila Palkar, Sharib Hashmi, and others. Actor Imran Khan also made his comeback to the big screen with the comedy-drama.</p>

